    <CriticalFlows>
      <VF-PLUGIN-INSTALL><Flow>DF-PLUGIN-INSTALL</Flow><Priority>high</Priority><Expected>Pinned plugin specifier, vv-controller default agent, managed agents/skills, tools.apply_patch false, role-reference model fields, and seeded vvoc schema v3.</Expected></VF-PLUGIN-INSTALL>
      <VF-CONFIG-SYNC><Flow>DF-CONFIG-SYNC</Flow><Priority>high</Priority><Expected>Canonical vvoc schema v3 is refreshed while role assignments and plugin toggles survive; invalid or old configs fail before rewrite.</Expected></VF-CONFIG-SYNC>
      <VF-STRICT-CURRENT-CUTOVER><Flow>DF-CONFIG-SYNC, DF-UPGRADE, DF-GUARDIAN-REVIEW, DF-HASHLINE-EDIT</Flow><Priority>high</Priority><Expected>Old configs, SDK paths, and hash algorithms fail loudly or are ignored rather than repaired or used as compatibility fallbacks.</Expected></VF-STRICT-CURRENT-CUTOVER>
      <VF-LAYERED-CONFIG><Flow>DF-LAYERED-CONFIG</Flow><Priority>high</Priority><Expected>Reads choose env, nearest project, global, then defaults where allowed; project writes stay inside selected project root.</Expected></VF-LAYERED-CONFIG>
      <VF-VVOC-LAUNCH><Flow>DF-VVOC-LAUNCH</Flow><Priority>high</Priority><Expected>Launch plan sets OPENCODE_CONFIG and VVOC_CONFIG, forwards args, preserves child exit code, and reports missing project layer with install hint.</Expected></VF-VVOC-LAUNCH>
      <VF-RELEASE-AUTOMATION><Flow>DF-RELEASE</Flow><Priority>high</Priority><Expected>release:bump and tag publish flow validate package version, schema id, changelog summary, quality checks, build, pack, and npm publish gating.</Expected></VF-RELEASE-AUTOMATION>
      <VF-ROLE-MANAGEMENT><Flow>DF-ROLE-MANAGEMENT</Flow><Priority>high</Priority><Expected>Built-in roles are visible, custom roles round-trip, concrete assignments normalize, and built-in role deletion is blocked.</Expected></VF-ROLE-MANAGEMENT>
      <VF-ROLE-RESOLUTION><Flow>DF-ROLE-RESOLUTION</Flow><Priority>high</Priority><Expected>Supported vv-role:* fields resolve to concrete model selections and unknown roles fail without fallback.</Expected></VF-ROLE-RESOLUTION>
      <VF-PRESET-SWITCH><Flow>DF-PRESET-SWITCH</Flow><Priority>high</Priority><Expected>Applying a preset mutates only listed roles and never rewrites OpenCode config directly.</Expected></VF-PRESET-SWITCH>
      <VF-HASHLINE-EDIT><Flow>DF-HASHLINE-EDIT</Flow><Priority>high</Priority><Expected>Read output emits current anchors, anchored edits preserve text envelope, and stale or old hash anchors are rejected.</Expected></VF-HASHLINE-EDIT>
      <VF-GUARDIAN-REVIEW><Flow>DF-GUARDIAN-REVIEW</Flow><Priority>high</Priority><Expected>Guardian resolves config/model, logs bounded markers, auto-allows only below threshold, and falls back to manual approval on higher risk or failure.</Expected></VF-GUARDIAN-REVIEW>
      <VF-SYSTEM-CONTEXT-INJECTION><Flow>DF-SYSTEM-CONTEXT</Flow><Priority>medium</Priority><Expected>Eligible primaries receive reusable guidance exactly once; known subagents are skipped.</Expected></VF-SYSTEM-CONTEXT-INJECTION>
      <VF-SECRETS-REDACTION><Flow>DF-SECRETS-REDACTION</Flow><Priority>high</Priority><Expected>Provider-bound payloads are redacted and local completions/tool execution restore placeholders where needed.</Expected></VF-SECRETS-REDACTION>
      <VF-WORKFLOW-TOOLS><Flow>DF-WORKFLOW-TOOLS</Flow><Priority>high</Priority><Expected>Work-item tools create deterministic IDs, enforce explicit mode/reviewers, list lifecycle metadata, and close only ready items.</Expected></VF-WORKFLOW-TOOLS>
      <VF-LAUNCH-ENFORCEMENT><Flow>DF-LAUNCH-ENFORCEMENT</Flow><Priority>high</Priority><Expected>Tracked launches require VVOC_WORK_ITEM_ID and valid state; invalid launches are rejected and untracked launches pass through.</Expected></VF-LAUNCH-ENFORCEMENT>
      <VF-RESULT-PARSING><Flow>DF-RESULT-PARSING</Flow><Priority>high</Priority><Expected>Tracked outputs parse strict top blocks, update explicit round state, repair only bounded resumable envelopes, and halt on malformed or hard-stop results.</Expected></VF-RESULT-PARSING>
      <VF-LOOP-GATE><Flow>DF-LOOP-GATE</Flow><Priority>high</Priority><Expected>Rounds one and two are allowed and round three is blocked deterministically without semantic heuristics.</Expected></VF-LOOP-GATE>
      <VF-WORKFLOW-PERSISTENCE><Flow>DF-WORKFLOW-PERSISTENCE</Flow><Priority>high</Priority><Expected>Per-session workflow state hydrates, snapshots, switches, and cleans up without throwing on missing or corrupt files.</Expected></VF-WORKFLOW-PERSISTENCE>
      <VF-PLUGIN-TOGGLE><Flow>DF-PLUGIN-TOGGLE, DF-PLUGIN-TOGGLE-CHECK</Flow><Priority>medium</Priority><Expected>Known plugins can be enabled or disabled, sync preserves values, list reports status, and disabled plugins return empty hooks.</Expected></VF-PLUGIN-TOGGLE>
    </CriticalFlows>
